### Module Dependency Rules

**CRITICAL: Follow These Dependency Rules**

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              :app                       │  ← Orchestrates everything
└────────────┬────────────────────────────┘
             │ depends on ↓
┌────────────▼────────────────────────────┐
│         :navigation                     │  ← Navigation coordinator
└────────────┬────────────────────────────┘
             │ depends on ↓
┌────────────▼────────────────────────────┐
│    :feature:* modules                   │  ← Feature modules (isolated)
└────────────┬────────────────────────────┘
             │ depends on ↓
┌────────────▼────────────────────────────┐
│         :core:* modules                 │  ← Core/shared modules
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘

Rules:
✅ Features can depend on core modules
✅ Features can depend on navigation (for deep links)
❌ Features CANNOT depend on other features
❌ Features CANNOT depend on :app
❌ Core modules cannot depend on features
✅ Use APIs/interfaces for feature-to-feature communication
```

