### Navigation Between Features

**Central Navigation Module**

```kotlin
// navigation/src/main/kotlin/com/yourapp/navigation/AppNavGraph.kt
@Composable
fun AppNavGraph(
    navController: NavHostController,
    modifier: Modifier = Modifier
) {
    NavHost(
        navController = navController,
        startDestination = KanbanDestinations.KANBAN_BOARD,
        modifier = modifier
    ) {
        // Kanban feature graph
        kanbanNavGraph(navController)
        
        // Notes feature graph
        notesNavGraph(navController)
        
        // Media feature graph
        mediaNavGraph(navController)
        
        // Task detail feature graph
        taskDetailNavGraph(navController)
    }
}

// Each feature provides its own nav graph
// feature/kanban/api/KanbanNavigation.kt
fun NavGraphBuilder.kanbanNavGraph(navController: NavController) {
    composable(KanbanDestinations.KANBAN_BOARD) {
        KanbanBoardScreen(
            onNavigateToTaskDetail = { taskId ->
                navController.navigate(TaskDetailDestinations.taskDetailRoute(taskId))
            },
            onNavigateToNotes = {
                navController.navigate(NotesDestinations.NOTES_LIST)
            }
        )
    }
}
```

### Event Bus for Cross-Feature Communication

**For decoupled event communication:**

```kotlin
// core/common/src/main/kotlin/com/yourapp/core/common/event/AppEvents.kt
sealed interface AppEvent {
    data class TaskCreated(val taskId: String) : AppEvent
    data class TaskUpdated(val taskId: String) : AppEvent
    data class TaskDeleted(val taskId: String) : AppEvent
    data class MediaAttached(val mediaId: String, val targetId: String) : AppEvent
    data class NoteLinked(val noteId: String, val taskId: String) : AppEvent
}

// core/common/src/main/kotlin/com/yourapp/core/common/event/EventBus.kt
@Singleton
class EventBus @Inject constructor() {
    private val _events = MutableSharedFlow<AppEvent>(
        replay = 0,
        extraBufferCapacity = 10,
        onBufferOverflow = BufferOverflow.DROP_OLDEST
    )
    
    val events: SharedFlow<AppEvent> = _events.asSharedFlow()
    
    suspend fun emit(event: AppEvent) {
        _events.emit(event)
    }
}

// Usage in feature module
@HiltViewModel
internal class KanbanViewModel @Inject constructor(
    private val repository: TaskRepository,
    private val eventBus: EventBus
) : ViewModel() {
    
    init {
        // Listen to events from other features
        viewModelScope.launch {
            eventBus.events.collect { event ->
                when (event) {
                    is AppEvent.NoteLinked -> {
                        // Refresh task with linked note
                        refreshTask(event.taskId)
                    }
                    is AppEvent.MediaAttached -> {
                        // Update task with new media
                    }
                    else -> {}
                }
            }
        }
    }
    
    fun createTask(task: Task) {
        viewModelScope.launch {
            repository.createTask(task)
            eventBus.emit(AppEvent.TaskCreated(task.id))
        }
    }
}
```

### Team Workflow & Ownership

**Feature Team Structure:**

```
Team 1: Kanban Board
- Owns: feature/kanban
- API: KanbanApi.kt (stable contract)
- Can work independently without affecting other teams

Team 2: Notes
- Owns: feature/notes
- API: NotesApi.kt
- Consumes: KanbanApi (read-only)

Team 3: Media Manager
- Owns: feature/media
- API: MediaApi.kt
- Consumes: KanbanApi, NotesApi

Team 4: Core/Infrastructure
- Owns: All core/* modules
- Maintains: Shared utilities, design system
```

**Development Workflow:**

1. **API-First Design**: Teams agree on API contracts before implementation
2. **Parallel Development**: Teams work on their features independently
3. **Mock Implementations**: Use fake/mock APIs during development
4. **Integration**: Only integrate when APIs are stable
5. **Code Reviews**: Each team reviews their own feature code

